{"id": 161, "title": "Ticket #161: Add VOMS support in Condor", "description": "<blockquote>\nEnable Condor to recognize <a class=\"external\" href=\"http://edg-wp2.web.cern.ch/edg-wp2/security/voms/\">Virtual Organization Membership Service</a> (VOMS) group/authorization extensions potentially embedded in the X509 credential associated with a job, and securely advertise these attributes in the job classad.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2009-Jan-30 12:29:11 by zmiller:</em> <br/>\n\ncoding is complete and tested by hand.  yet to do is to add the external and check everything in.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2009-May-05 17:26:58 by zmiller:</em> <br/>\n\ncurrent code works, but is not sufficient.  it turns out any character is valid in an X.509 subject name, so using : as a separator isn't going to work.  instead, i need to add some sort of quoting mechanism.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2009-Nov-11 17:25:07 by zmiller:</em> <br/>\n\nsee derived tickets for problems that must be fixed before 7.4.1.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=724\" title=\"Can't submit jobs with proxies on platforms without voms\">#724</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nCan't submit jobs with proxies on platforms without voms</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=727\" title=\"VOMS support not documented\">#727</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nVOMS support not documented</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktvi